 # Shell Command Configuration Rule
This rule defines which shell to use and what types of commands can be executed automatically.

## Shell Configuration
- Default shell: PowerShell
- Location: System PowerShell

## Allowed Command Types
The following command types are allowed for automatic execution:
- Compilation commands
- Git commands
- Yarn commands
- Other safe commands

## Configuration
```json
{
    "shell": "powershell",
    "shellCommands": {
        "compilation": true,
        "git": true,
        "yarn": true,
        "safe": true
    }
}
```

## File Pattern
*.ps1, *.cmd, *.bat